Dissolve gelatin in boiling water completely. Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1-1/4 cups ice and water. Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened. Remove any unmelted ice. If mixture is still thin, refrigerate until slightly thickened. Place fruit on bottom of 4 dessert dishes. Pour thickened gelatin over fruit. Suspend gummy fish in gelatin. Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour. Garnish with additional gummy fish, if desired.